claim.claim-text:
A process for producing hemicellulose sugars and energy from cellulosic biomass, said process comprising:
(a) extracting hemicelluloses from cellulosic biomass with steam, to produce a cellulose-rich solids stream and a liquid extract comprising water and said hemicelluloses;
(b) concentrating said liquid extract in a first evaporation stage that removes water from said liquid extract, to produce a first concentrated extract, wherein said first evaporation stage is operated at a pH below 4.8, and wherein a first amount of acetic acid is evaporated from said first evaporation stage;
(c) hydrolyzing said first concentrated extract from step (b) in the presence of sulfuric acid, heat, or enzymes, to produce a hydrolyzate comprising hemicellulose monomer sugars and acetyl groups;
(d) introducing the hydrolyzate from step (c) to a second evaporation stage, to produce a second concentrated extract, wherein said second evaporation stage is operated at a pH of 3 - 4.8, wherein a second amount of acetic acid is evaporated from said second evaporation stage, and wherein said concentrated extract comprises said hemicellulose sugars;
(e) dewatering said cellulose-rich solids stream from step (a), to produce dewatered solids; and
(f) combusting said dewatered solids, to produce energy.
